---
description: Next.js API, validation, and observability standards
globs: app/api/**/*.ts,app/**/*.tsx,instrumentation*.ts,sentry*.config.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

- Treat route handlers as trust boundaries: validate form fields, query params, headers, and payloads before using them.
- Return structured 4xx responses for expected user or client mistakes; reserve thrown exceptions for unexpected failures.
- Capture useful operational context for server-side failures, but never include secrets, tokens, raw file contents, or unnecessary personal data.
- Preserve Sentry wiring when changing request, error, or image-processing flows.
- Keep client-facing error messages clear and actionable without exposing stack traces or internal service details.
- Use typed constants or narrow unions for request options shared between UI and API code.
